what is delta lake ?
Delta Lake is an open-source storage layer built on top of Parquet files that adds reliability features such as ACID transactions, schema enforcement, schema evolution, time travel, and support for concurrent reads and writes.

Parquet Files
      +
Transaction Log
(_delta_log)
      =
Delta Lake

ADLS is where data is stored.

Delta Lake is how data is managed inside that storage.

Delta Lake itself is not a storage service. Delta tables are typically stored on ADLS Gen2. Delta Lake provides the transaction layer and table-management capabilities on top of the underlying storage.

